                <note rend="inline" type="source">124.93/1–2749: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stuart</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-01-27T19:00:00-05:00"
                            >January 27, 1949—7 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>116. In view ur 240 Jan 27 Dept will act on recommendations contained in (2)
                    urtel 187 Jan 22 as amended by second para urtel 217 Jan 26. Telegraphic
                    instruction going out tonight.</p>
                <p>In view considerations mentioned Deptel 95 Jan 26 you are instructed implement
                    these transfers in manner to draw as little notice as possible and in
                    association with movement to Canton.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
